19/12/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- State Department spokesman Richard Boucher said Thursday (18 December) that Washington expects the prison sentences handed down this week to members of the 17 November terrorist group in Greece to be fully served, without any intervention. On Wednesday, a Greek anti-terrorist court sentenced the leader and the chief assassin of the leftist group to multiple life terms. (Ekathimerini - 19/12/03; AP, AFP, BTA - 18/12/03)
